  "text": "Note that the intersection of each R f (Θ i ) and K f is either a critical point or the union of critical internal rays, then the following result is straightforward. With these preparations, we can prove the key lemma below. Note that for any angle x ∈ V G , by (1) and (3) of Proposition 6.5, the landing point γ g (x) of the ray R g (x) belongs to T . Lemma 6. [CITATION_1] . Let x, y be two distinct points in V G .",
